h3. Problem Definition
When builds are deployed from Bamboo, the version is not updated in Jira's {{fixVersion}} field.

h3. Suggested Solution
Update Jira link to include fixVersion if available.

h3. Why this is important
This allows for automation, and limited manual intervention in Bamboo or Jira. 
 
h3. Workaround 
Add a Script task to make a PUT rest call to {{<jira-url>/rest/api/2/issue/<issue-key>}}, using the following JSON payload:
{noformat}
{
    "update": {
        "fixVersions" : [
            {"add":
                {"name" : "${bamboo.deploy.version}"}
            }
        ]
    }
}{noformat}

h3. Summary
[/agent/assignment - Bamboo REST API documentation|https://docs.atlassian.com/bamboo/REST/6.1.0/#d2e2427]

We are able to receive the response in the *application/json* format, but we can't make the request to the server using content in this format.


h3. Request with parameters in line (works)
{code:title=Request}
curl -u <user>:<passwd> \
     -X POST "http://localhost:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/agent/assignment?executorType=AGENT&executorId=196609&assignmentType=DEPLOYMENT_PROJECT&entityId=3637249"
{code}

{code:title=Response}
{"nameElements":["QA and DEV"],"description":"","executableType":"DEPLOYMENT_PROJECT","id":3637249,"executableId":3637249,"executableTypeLabel":"Deployment project","executorType":"AGENT","executorId":196609,"capabilitiesMatch":true}
{code}

h3. Request using "Content-Type: application/json" (fails)
{code:title=Request}
curl -u <user>:<passwd> \
       -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
       -d '{"executorType":"AGENT","executorId":"196609","assignmentType":"DEPLOYMENT_PROJECT","entityId":"3637249"}' \
       -X POST http://localhost:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/agent/assignment
{code}

{code:title=Response}
{"errors":["executorType query parameter is mandatory"],"fieldErrors":{}}{code}   

h3. More ...
As noticed in https://www.reddit.com/r/atlassian/comments/b1s1x2/bamboo_agent_assignment_automation/ we expect numerical ids for executable while we don't expose neither plan or job ids in our REST API. This API shall accept plan/job keys as well.

